[SN]TITLE[SN]
Witness plea over Eddleston scooter accident

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man has been seriously injured after falling from his scooter in the Scottish Borders.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The incident happened near the village of Eddleston at about 13:00 on Sunday.
The man fell from a Vespa scooter and was taken to Edinburgh Royal Infirmary for treatment.
Police said they believed a black car may have been involved in the incident and appealed for anyone who was in the area to contact them.
